    {
      "id": "2398828ded5b6a05d2bcbddff8195aee586f8b24",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-11 18:08:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThis fails conf-sanity.sh test_50h() with:\n\n lustre-OST0000-osc-[!M]*/active: Found no match\n\nand on MDS console:\n\n 145-0: Couldn't find lustre-OST0000 inlog (1). No permanent changes were made to the config log.\n\nlooks like this patch is to blame?  I'm not a huge fan of abusing the label like this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "0d55b8db7bdfd94aef2675bd487d793a20d10853",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-11 18:20:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> looks like this patch is to blame? \n\nchecking ..\n\n> I'm not a huge fan of abusing the label like this.\n\ncan't disagree on this. any options are welcome. at the moment the significant problem is that params are stored in totally different ways: single file with ldiskfs and set of attributes with zfs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "6b2ab5aefbf817328ff0d33c62cadacf26831392",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-12 17:56:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nFor now I'm marking this patch -1 until we come up with a better solution.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "6e8b7a89d8f6a38f765592d50520594f15a1e54d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-12 17:58:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIt also looks like this patch caused some failures in conf-sanity.sh:\n\n   Read previous values:\n Target:     lustre=OST0000\n Lustre FS:  lustre\n Mount type: ldiskfs\n Flags:      0x42\n              (OST update )\n Persistent mount opts: errors=remount-ro\n Parameters: mgsnode=10.10.16.152@tcp sys.timeout=20\n\n   Permanent disk data:\n Target:     lustre^OST0000\n Lustre FS:  lustre\n Mount type: ldiskfs\n Flags:      0x42",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "9cb1d04c6af7f36c3b9c447f7d419f1ff7ea4bec",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-12 19:44:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI'm not a fan of this approach either, I'm fine to think of an option. it will take a bit though..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
